1
00:00:13,358 --> 00:00:16,558
[Joo In Ah is in an inappropriate relationship
with a coworker]

2
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,070
[From: NONAME]

3
00:00:38,422 --> 00:00:39,993
[Send]

4
00:00:39,993 --> 00:00:42,495
[Your email has been sent successfully]

5
00:00:48,970 --> 00:00:50,347
[Joo In Ah]

6
00:00:50,347 --> 00:00:51,813
[An inappropriate relationship with a coworker]

7
00:00:51,813 --> 00:00:54,223
[Haemu Planning Office] [Haemu Marketing Team]
[Haemu Audit Team 1]

8
00:01:00,388 --> 00:01:01,909
[Send]

9
00:01:08,993 --> 00:01:09,946
[Seung Hee]

10
00:01:12,817 --> 00:01:14,466
- Hello?
- Ah Jeong.

11
00:01:14,466 --> 00:01:16,862
Check out the article I just sent you.

12
00:01:21,159 --> 00:01:23,954
[Haemu Group's eldest son pushed out?
Sibling rivalry escalates]

13
00:01:25,163 --> 00:01:26,530
Did you call PR yet?

14
00:01:26,530 --> 00:01:29,501
Find out exactly where this came from
and how it got published.

15
00:01:29,501 --> 00:01:31,398
I'll call Legal.

16
00:01:52,977 --> 00:01:54,734
In Ah.

17
00:02:01,074 --> 00:02:04,094
Can I help you?
I'm cleaning the room right now.

18
00:02:06,257 --> 00:02:07,784
Sir?

19
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:36,847
Why are you staring at me like that?

20
00:02:36,847 --> 00:02:38,126
I mean,

21
00:02:38,126 --> 00:02:40,912
I know I'm handsome, but...

22
00:02:52,356 --> 00:02:53,835
What are you doing?

23
00:02:53,835 --> 00:02:56,068
Just making sure this is real.

24
00:02:57,138 --> 00:03:01,078
How did you show up right when I needed you?

25
00:03:03,358 --> 00:03:05,649
This is seriously crazy.

26
00:03:05,649 --> 00:03:07,223
What moment was that?

27
00:03:07,223 --> 00:03:09,851
The moment I realized I missed you.

28
00:03:13,768 --> 00:03:17,067
How do you say things like that

29
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:19,840
with such a straight face?

30
00:03:24,236 --> 00:03:26,117
Honestly, I've been regretting it.

31
00:03:26,117 --> 00:03:28,690
Not being honest about how I felt...

32
00:03:29,662 --> 00:03:32,081
I wanted to fix things,

33
00:03:32,081 --> 00:03:33,792
but I thought it was too late.

34
00:03:33,792 --> 00:03:36,616
So it really got to me.

35
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:38,440
But then...

36
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:41,347
I started missing you like crazy.

37
00:03:41,347 --> 00:03:44,938
And right then, you showed up.

38
00:03:44,938 --> 00:03:47,338
I could feel you missing me too,

39
00:03:47,338 --> 00:03:50,513
and I didn't want to waste another second.

40
00:03:55,171 --> 00:03:57,857
Thanks for coming.

41
00:04:03,279 --> 00:04:04,765
First things first,

42
00:04:04,765 --> 00:04:06,965
let's fix this one step at a time.

43
00:04:06,965 --> 00:04:10,362
I'm not taking that U.S. assignment.
No matter what.

44
00:04:10,362 --> 00:04:12,328
And if they try to force me to go,

45
00:04:12,328 --> 00:04:15,097
I'll stage a sit-in or something.

46
00:04:17,726 --> 00:04:19,983
But honestly...

47
00:04:19,983 --> 00:04:22,983
career-wise, it is a great opportunity.

48
00:04:22,983 --> 00:04:25,816
Didn't we agree to be honest now?

49
00:04:26,936 --> 00:04:29,280
So you'd really be okay
with me going to the States?

50
00:04:30,818 --> 00:04:32,845
No. Don't go.

51
00:04:32,845 --> 00:04:35,881
Stay right here next to me.

52
00:04:35,881 --> 00:04:37,403
Gladly.

53
00:04:57,065 --> 00:05:00,091
- That's it?
- Yeah, that's it.

54
00:05:01,397 --> 00:05:03,785
No kiss on this side too?

55
00:05:28,448 --> 00:05:31,910
[Episode 9: Love Dive]

56
00:05:44,206 --> 00:05:47,168
We only said goodbye a little while ago,

57
00:05:47,168 --> 00:05:48,897
and you already miss me?

58
00:05:48,897 --> 00:05:51,717
Yeah. I miss you.

59
00:05:54,788 --> 00:05:58,018
- My heart just skipped a beat.
- Just from that?

60
00:05:58,018 --> 00:06:00,462
You better brace yourself.

61
00:06:00,462 --> 00:06:04,384
Once I start dating someone, I go all in.

62
00:06:05,442 --> 00:06:07,503
Wow, figures...

63
00:06:07,503 --> 00:06:10,869
Dating you really is on another level.

64
00:06:11,529 --> 00:06:13,476
But I'm not exactly easy either.

65
00:06:13,476 --> 00:06:16,167
So you should prepare yourself too, ma'am.

66
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:18,115
Yeah?

67
00:06:18,115 --> 00:06:20,655
What should I prepare for first?

68
00:06:22,409 --> 00:06:25,160
Maybe we should start with
how we call each other.

69
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,447
I don't want to keep calling you "ma'am."

70
00:06:27,447 --> 00:06:29,560
It's way too formal.

71
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,583
Ms. In Ah?

72
00:06:33,287 --> 00:06:35,432
Or In Ah...

73
00:06:35,432 --> 00:06:37,495
Actually, now that I think about it,

74
00:06:37,495 --> 00:06:40,188
your name's really pretty.

75
00:06:40,188 --> 00:06:42,328
Joo In Ah.

76
00:06:49,446 --> 00:06:51,706
- Drink up.
- Cheers!

77
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:58,675
Jeon Jae Yeol. What's gotten into you?

78
00:06:58,675 --> 00:07:01,652
We call you out all the time,
and you never show.

79
00:07:01,652 --> 00:07:03,889
Yeah, I know. I deserved that.

80
00:07:03,889 --> 00:07:06,134
My bad.

81
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:09,127
Hey, hey, slow down.

82
00:07:09,127 --> 00:07:11,730
Aren't you going a little too hard?

83
00:07:11,730 --> 00:07:12,754
Is this because...

84
00:07:12,754 --> 00:07:15,627
your brother got named co-vice chairman?

85
00:07:15,627 --> 00:07:17,111
Yeah, I saw the article.

86
00:07:17,111 --> 00:07:21,061
Man, your dad really should've
just settled it cleanly.

87
00:07:21,061 --> 00:07:22,599
What's with the co-vice chairmen thing?

88
00:07:22,599 --> 00:07:24,745
He's basically pitting you two
against each other.

89
00:07:24,745 --> 00:07:27,262
I said let's drink.
Why are you guys talking so much?

90
00:07:27,262 --> 00:07:28,425
- Okay.
- Drink.

91
00:07:28,425 --> 00:07:29,465
Yeah.

92
00:07:29,465 --> 00:07:31,909
It's not every day he comes out like this.

93
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,259
Let's drink.

94
00:07:33,259 --> 00:07:35,146
Cheers.

95
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:29,544
Cold?

96
00:08:36,245 --> 00:08:38,529
Is it really that good?

97
00:08:38,529 --> 00:08:39,872
Yeah.

98
00:08:42,229 --> 00:08:45,773
Never thought I'd live to see the day
I'd look forward to going to work.

99
00:08:45,773 --> 00:08:47,163
Really?

100
00:08:47,163 --> 00:08:49,010
I like going to work.

101
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:51,832
It's way more fun than
sitting around at home bored.

102
00:08:51,832 --> 00:08:53,694
Amazing.

103
00:08:53,694 --> 00:08:56,098
I can see the crazy in your eyes already.

104
00:08:58,392 --> 00:08:59,590
But from now on,

105
00:08:59,590 --> 00:09:03,127
you'll have way more fun things than just work.

106
00:09:03,127 --> 00:09:06,271
First of all, clear your entire weekend.

107
00:09:06,271 --> 00:09:08,658
I mean, we went all the way to Jeju

108
00:09:08,658 --> 00:09:11,202
and came right back.

109
00:09:11,202 --> 00:09:13,512
I booked us a private villa in Sokcho.

110
00:09:13,512 --> 00:09:16,536
Let's take it slow, enjoy the ocean,

111
00:09:16,536 --> 00:09:18,285
get some fresh air.

112
00:09:19,282 --> 00:09:21,863
Wait... overnight?

113
00:09:25,834 --> 00:09:27,291
Well...

114
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:31,031
A day trip just didn't feel like enough.

115
00:09:36,141 --> 00:09:38,035
That sounds amazing.

116
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:44,926
Although now I'm kind of worried.

117
00:09:44,926 --> 00:09:47,823
I'm worried it'll be way too obvious at work
how much I like you.

118
00:09:47,823 --> 00:09:50,580
- What do I do?
- I kind of want to see that.

119
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:52,780
I want to see how obvious you get.

120
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:55,765
Don't smile like that.

121
00:09:55,765 --> 00:09:59,411
When you smile like that,
I smile too, and it totally gives us away.

122
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:04,668
Seriously, what am I supposed to do at work?

123
00:10:05,378 --> 00:10:07,629
Obvious, my ass.

124
00:10:19,028 --> 00:10:21,387
At work, Joo In Ah was...

125
00:10:22,005 --> 00:10:24,062
still Joo In Ah,

126
00:10:24,062 --> 00:10:26,426
relationship or not.

127
00:10:26,426 --> 00:10:29,383
So what's the conclusion here?

128
00:10:29,383 --> 00:10:32,847
It's not here, not here...

129
00:10:32,847 --> 00:10:33,911
There's nothing!

130
00:10:33,911 --> 00:10:36,000
Where's the key point?

131
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,818
Can you see it?

132
00:10:37,818 --> 00:10:40,595
Do you see the point of this report?

133
00:10:41,976 --> 00:10:45,766
A report like this shouldn't get paid for.
You should be paying to write it.

134
00:10:45,766 --> 00:10:48,135
What a waste of paper.

135
00:10:48,135 --> 00:10:49,853
Do it again!

136
00:11:13,213 --> 00:11:15,236
Mr. Noh, are you okay?

137
00:11:16,068 --> 00:11:17,360
Ki Jun,

138
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:19,799
did you get on her bad side again or something?

139
00:11:19,799 --> 00:11:23,036
No. He just works too hard.

140
00:11:23,036 --> 00:11:26,213
Hey, you should learn from me...

141
00:11:26,213 --> 00:11:28,070
and just wing it verbally.

142
00:11:28,070 --> 00:11:30,780
The harder you work, the worse it is for you.

143
00:11:30,780 --> 00:11:33,546
The more you accomplish,
the more they can use against you.

144
00:11:34,433 --> 00:11:36,890
Such wise words.

145
00:11:36,890 --> 00:11:38,680
Funny how someone who barely works

146
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:43,030
claims the most overtime pay
and field support expenses on the team.

147
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:45,314
Hey, that's enough.

148
00:11:45,314 --> 00:11:46,709
Ms. Yoon.

149
00:11:46,709 --> 00:11:49,162
You finished the PT
for the company club audit report?

150
00:11:49,162 --> 00:11:51,566
Yes. I already emailed the final version.

151
00:11:51,566 --> 00:11:53,444
Nice work.

152
00:11:53,444 --> 00:11:57,210
You loaded it up with flashy charts, graphs,
and animations, huh?

153
00:11:57,832 --> 00:12:00,267
You're always reliable, Ms. Yoon.

154
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,733
Good job.

155
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:02,823
Anyway,

156
00:12:02,823 --> 00:12:07,053
later when we go brief the head,
let's all head in together, okay?

157
00:12:07,053 --> 00:12:08,990
You too, Ki Jun.

158
00:12:08,990 --> 00:12:11,787
Head Joo is actually a really good person.

159
00:12:11,787 --> 00:12:13,892
So don't be too nervous around her, okay?

160
00:12:13,892 --> 00:12:15,492
Yeah.

161
00:12:16,452 --> 00:12:18,518
Yes, she's great.

162
00:12:24,225 --> 00:12:26,347
Almost too great.

163
00:12:45,356 --> 00:12:46,886
Secretary Park.

164
00:12:48,096 --> 00:12:50,266
- Yes, sir?
- So when exactly...

165
00:12:50,266 --> 00:12:52,581
is Vice Chairman Jae Yeol planning to show up?

166
00:12:52,581 --> 00:12:55,634
He's not feeling well,

167
00:12:56,496 --> 00:12:59,667
I'll brief him on everything
discussed in the meeting.

168
00:13:03,178 --> 00:13:04,941
Okay.

169
00:13:04,941 --> 00:13:07,921
We can't sit around waiting forever.

170
00:13:14,871 --> 00:13:16,895
Let's get started without him.

171
00:13:16,895 --> 00:13:20,532
And don't forget, I'm a vice chairman too.

172
00:13:20,532 --> 00:13:23,856
Yes, I think we should begin.

173
00:13:23,856 --> 00:13:25,880
Secretary Park, you may leave now.

174
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:27,537
- But...
- A secretary has no authority

175
00:13:27,537 --> 00:13:31,171
to attend a meeting
on a vice chairman's behalf.

176
00:13:49,472 --> 00:13:50,729
[Vice Chairman]

177
00:13:53,953 --> 00:13:56,248
[Park Ah Jeong, Secretary's Office]

178
00:14:55,014 --> 00:14:57,991
Wow, there were so many.

179
00:14:57,991 --> 00:15:00,288
- Did you see them?
- Yeah, it was insane.

180
00:15:00,288 --> 00:15:01,928
It was unbelievable.

181
00:15:01,928 --> 00:15:04,448
- Right?
- Yeah. You saw them too?

182
00:15:04,448 --> 00:15:06,307
- Yeah, I did.
- What's that?

183
00:15:17,946 --> 00:15:19,770
- You're here.
- Yeah.

184
00:15:19,770 --> 00:15:21,458
Did you have fun?

185
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,884
- Is Seo Yeon asleep?
- Yeah.

186
00:15:25,111 --> 00:15:28,361
Her preschool has a cooking class on the 29th.

187
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:30,142
You can make it, right?

188
00:15:34,604 --> 00:15:37,055
- I have diving club that day.
- Again?

189
00:15:37,055 --> 00:15:40,035
You've been going diving an awful lot lately.

190
00:15:42,318 --> 00:15:44,655
Can't you skip it just once?

191
00:15:44,655 --> 00:15:47,317
I had to go to her speech contest alone
last time too.

192
00:15:47,317 --> 00:15:50,783
- She was really upset that you didn't come.
- Next time.

193
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,433
I'll join next time.

194
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:56,224
You really are going diving, right?

195
00:15:56,224 --> 00:15:58,331
You're not up to something else, are you?

196
00:16:14,802 --> 00:16:15,844
[Audit Overview]

197
00:16:15,844 --> 00:16:16,857
[Types of Violations]

198
00:16:16,857 --> 00:16:20,976
We found four cases where rookie or
contract workers were listed as ghost members

199
00:16:20,976 --> 00:16:24,531
to fraudulently collect company club funding.

200
00:16:24,531 --> 00:16:26,749
There were also seven cases

201
00:16:26,749 --> 00:16:29,060
where club officers pocketed activity funds

202
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:31,585
or personally profited
from rental and lesson fees.

203
00:16:32,403 --> 00:16:35,720
We also found eight cases
where employees used club activities

204
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:37,477
to boost sales for friends'
or family businesses,

205
00:16:37,477 --> 00:16:41,391
plus two cases involving
gambling-related issues.

206
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:47,457
Right now, club activity reports
are only submitted once a year, right?

207
00:16:47,457 --> 00:16:48,511
Yes, right.

208
00:16:48,511 --> 00:16:50,421
From now on,
have them submitted quarterly instead.

209
00:16:50,421 --> 00:16:53,524
And ask HR to require
more detailed reporting as well.

210
00:16:53,524 --> 00:16:55,302
Yes, I'll pass that along.

211
00:16:55,302 --> 00:16:58,848
Also, there's the PM issue
involving the clubs...

212
00:17:00,254 --> 00:17:03,412
This is a tip from the wife of
Mr. Min Tae Woo from Haemu International.

213
00:17:03,412 --> 00:17:06,421
She says her husband's become obsessed with
the company scuba diving club,

214
00:17:06,421 --> 00:17:08,952
and she's not sure
it's an innocent hobby group anymore.

215
00:17:08,952 --> 00:17:11,209
It's hard to tell because of the gear,

216
00:17:11,209 --> 00:17:13,209
but the guy on the right is definitely Mr. Min.

217
00:17:13,209 --> 00:17:16,446
And the person on the left
is suspected to be the affair partner.

218
00:17:16,446 --> 00:17:19,050
She found a bunch of photos of
that person on his phone.

219
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:20,960
Couldn't they just be hobby friends?

220
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,830
It does sound suspicious.

221
00:17:22,830 --> 00:17:25,460
The guy didn't even like water before,
could barely swim, apparently,

222
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:28,544
and now he never misses a scuba club meeting.

223
00:17:28,544 --> 00:17:30,974
Sometimes he even takes PTO to go.

224
00:17:30,974 --> 00:17:33,338
Then he comes home exhausted all the time.

225
00:17:33,338 --> 00:17:37,801
And apparently he keeps getting calls
late at night or at dawn and rushing out.

226
00:17:37,801 --> 00:17:40,878
People already say
these clubs are basically affair hotbeds.

227
00:17:40,878 --> 00:17:44,475
Like the club funding's paying for affairs.

228
00:17:44,475 --> 00:17:47,604
So how about we investigate this one
as a representative case?

229
00:17:47,604 --> 00:17:50,996
If we call him in,
he'll just deny everything anyway.

230
00:17:52,569 --> 00:17:56,543
Let's join the club ourselves
and see what's really going on.

231
00:17:57,553 --> 00:17:59,043
Mr. Noh,

232
00:17:59,043 --> 00:18:01,207
do you scuba dive?

233
00:18:01,954 --> 00:18:04,511
I tried it once on vacation a long time ago.

234
00:18:04,511 --> 00:18:07,207
Then go check out Mr. Min's club this weekend.

235
00:18:07,207 --> 00:18:08,318
What?

236
00:18:11,101 --> 00:18:13,678
I actually have...

237
00:18:14,306 --> 00:18:17,303
an important appointment this weekend.

238
00:18:18,818 --> 00:18:20,076
Really?

239
00:18:20,918 --> 00:18:24,082
Then does anyone else here know scuba diving?

240
00:18:24,082 --> 00:18:26,212
I have a water allergy.

241
00:18:26,212 --> 00:18:27,525
The ocean's just...

242
00:18:27,525 --> 00:18:30,245
I almost drowned in a river as a kid,
so I still have trauma from that.

243
00:18:30,245 --> 00:18:32,022
I can't equalize properly.

244
00:18:32,022 --> 00:18:34,668
And I refuse to work weekends.

245
00:18:36,426 --> 00:18:38,496
Oh, really?

246
00:18:38,496 --> 00:18:40,700
Well, I guess there's no helping it.

247
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:43,404
I like scuba diving anyway.

248
00:18:43,404 --> 00:18:45,597
- I'll go myself.
- Sorry?

249
00:18:52,359 --> 00:18:56,876
You don't have plans this weekend?

250
00:18:56,876 --> 00:18:59,883
Well, nothing really special this week...

251
00:18:59,883 --> 00:19:03,513
Clear your entire weekend.
I booked us a private villa in Sokcho.

252
00:19:03,513 --> 00:19:05,939
Guess not anymore...

253
00:19:08,873 --> 00:19:11,198
So you did have plans.

254
00:19:11,198 --> 00:19:13,948
That's harsh.

255
00:19:13,948 --> 00:19:17,825
Come on,
isn't it nice we still get to go together?

256
00:19:17,825 --> 00:19:20,249
And it's basically the same thing
we planned anyway.

257
00:19:20,249 --> 00:19:23,227
Ocean, fresh air... plus work.

258
00:19:23,227 --> 00:19:26,518
Killing two birds with one stone. Right?

259
00:19:26,518 --> 00:19:27,553
By the way,

260
00:19:27,553 --> 00:19:30,010
You said once you start dating, you burn hot.

261
00:19:30,010 --> 00:19:31,700
But all you've done is work me to death.

262
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:34,463
I thought I was about to burn out for real.

263
00:19:34,463 --> 00:19:36,509
That's because
we had that business trip last week,

264
00:19:36,509 --> 00:19:39,298
so work's been extra busy this week.

265
00:19:39,298 --> 00:19:42,516
And I was trying to keep a poker face at work
so it wouldn't be obvious.

266
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:46,080
So committed to the act
you forgot our weekend plans too?

267
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:50,720
It's just...
having weekend plans is still new to me.

268
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,177
And this is work, huh?

269
00:19:52,177 --> 00:19:54,590
I'm very strict about separating
work and personal life.

270
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,860
Right, understood, ma'am.

271
00:19:56,860 --> 00:19:59,410
Since this isn't a trip,
but a business assignment,

272
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:02,783
I'll remain completely professional today.

273
00:20:05,377 --> 00:20:07,953
Ki Jun, are you actually mad?

274
00:20:07,953 --> 00:20:09,104
Yes.

275
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:12,075
You idiot!

276
00:20:12,075 --> 00:20:13,105
Dummy!

277
00:20:13,105 --> 00:20:15,721
How do you forget your first date?

278
00:20:15,721 --> 00:20:17,476
- Pull yourself together, Joo In Ah!
- Hey, stop.

279
00:20:17,476 --> 00:20:19,046
Why are you hitting yourself?

280
00:20:19,046 --> 00:20:20,407
No, I had that coming.

281
00:20:20,407 --> 00:20:22,299
- Idiot! Dummy!
- Stop, stop.

282
00:20:22,299 --> 00:20:23,932
- Idiot! Dummy!
- Hey.

283
00:20:23,932 --> 00:20:26,094
I'm kidding, yeah.

284
00:20:26,094 --> 00:20:27,638
I'm not mad at all.

285
00:20:27,638 --> 00:20:29,431
- I was joking.
- You looked super mad.

286
00:20:29,431 --> 00:20:32,634
No, no. I'm not even sulking.

287
00:20:32,634 --> 00:20:34,607
I really am sorry.

288
00:20:36,488 --> 00:20:38,388
Beats me.

289
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:46,922
Alright, we've got some new faces today.

290
00:20:46,922 --> 00:20:49,888
Please welcome Head Joo In Ah from HQ Audit,

291
00:20:49,888 --> 00:20:53,098
and Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun.

292
00:20:53,098 --> 00:20:54,790
Nice to meet you all.

293
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:56,362
Let's give them a hand!

294
00:20:56,362 --> 00:21:00,289
Now, hearing Audit's here
might make some people nervous, but...

295
00:21:00,289 --> 00:21:03,780
We keep our books clean,
so we've got nothing to hide.

296
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:06,027
- Right, everyone?
- Yeah.

297
00:21:06,027 --> 00:21:09,564
Hey, you know saying that
just makes us sound guiltier, huh?

298
00:21:09,564 --> 00:21:10,849
You've got a point.

299
00:21:10,849 --> 00:21:14,502
Alright, since we've got a smaller group today,
we'll all board together.

300
00:21:14,502 --> 00:21:16,457
Everyone, double-check your gear first.

301
00:21:16,457 --> 00:21:18,114
- Okay!
- Okay!

302
00:21:46,956 --> 00:21:48,678
And since we use the buddy system,

303
00:21:48,678 --> 00:21:52,891
it'd probably be best for you
to pair up with experienced divers.

304
00:21:52,891 --> 00:21:56,464
Then I'll buddy up with Mr. Min.

305
00:21:56,464 --> 00:21:59,237
He seems pretty reliable.

306
00:21:59,237 --> 00:22:02,287
Alright then, Mr. Min and Mr. Noh are buddies.

307
00:22:02,287 --> 00:22:04,025
- Got it.
- Then your buddy will be...

308
00:22:04,025 --> 00:22:05,639
I'll do it.

309
00:22:28,639 --> 00:22:31,309
Mr. Min and Assistant Manager Ha
seem pretty close, huh?

310
00:22:31,309 --> 00:22:33,202
Yeah, they do.

311
00:22:34,972 --> 00:22:36,323
Why? Jealous?

312
00:22:36,323 --> 00:22:37,936
Because Assistant Manager Ha's your type?

313
00:22:37,936 --> 00:22:39,569
What?

314
00:22:39,569 --> 00:22:43,299
I saw you earlier. Your eyes were glued to her.

315
00:22:43,299 --> 00:22:47,179
So was that professionally motivated too?

316
00:22:47,179 --> 00:22:51,169
Come on, it wasn't like that.

317
00:22:51,169 --> 00:22:53,173
I was being completely professional.

318
00:22:53,173 --> 00:22:57,489
I was just checking
if she might be the person from the photo.

319
00:22:58,367 --> 00:22:59,950
See you later.

320
00:23:01,947 --> 00:23:03,521
In private.

321
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:11,177
Alright, let's get ready to dive.
Check your gear, everyone.

322
00:23:11,177 --> 00:23:12,911
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

323
00:25:40,057 --> 00:25:41,823
Are you okay?

324
00:25:53,797 --> 00:25:56,951
You looked like
you were having a panic attack earlier.

325
00:25:56,951 --> 00:25:59,518
Do you have claustrophobia or something?

326
00:25:59,518 --> 00:26:01,942
I'm fine. It's not that serious.

327
00:26:01,942 --> 00:26:04,176
Did you tell the instructor?

328
00:26:04,176 --> 00:26:07,377
For everyone's safety,
you should probably let people know.

329
00:26:07,377 --> 00:26:09,490
I said it's not that serious.

330
00:26:10,883 --> 00:26:14,227
Are you worried people might find out

331
00:26:14,227 --> 00:26:16,778
and stop you from diving?

332
00:26:16,778 --> 00:26:18,257
Do you really like diving that much?

333
00:26:18,257 --> 00:26:21,114
You sure are nosy for a first-timer.

334
00:26:21,114 --> 00:26:24,107
I can handle my own problems.

335
00:26:24,107 --> 00:26:26,092
So stay out of it.

336
00:26:47,048 --> 00:26:48,712
So there's a woman in the club,

337
00:26:48,712 --> 00:26:52,245
and even though he's claustrophobic,
he's forcing himself to dive?

338
00:26:52,245 --> 00:26:54,709
I mean, if he's really into diving,
I guess it's possible.

339
00:26:54,709 --> 00:26:57,687
It gives him an excuse
to openly spend time with her too.

340
00:26:59,088 --> 00:27:01,931
Assistant Manager Ha seemed like
a total veteran.

341
00:27:01,931 --> 00:27:04,145
Actually, that would make sense then.

342
00:27:04,145 --> 00:27:05,889
Maybe Mr. Min liked her first,

343
00:27:05,889 --> 00:27:08,672
found out about her hobby,
and joined the club because of her.

344
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:13,835
Wow, if that's really the case,

345
00:27:13,835 --> 00:27:16,630
that's basically a life-risking affair.

346
00:27:16,630 --> 00:27:17,964
Oh, I'm really sorry.

347
00:27:17,964 --> 00:27:21,000
I wanted to have dinner with everyone,
but an old coworker's father passed away,

348
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:21,982
so I need to head back.

349
00:27:21,982 --> 00:27:24,209
Good work today, everyone.
See you all on the next tour.

350
00:27:24,209 --> 00:27:25,666
- Okay, drive safe.
- See you next time.

351
00:27:25,666 --> 00:27:27,279
- See you next time.
- Bye.

352
00:27:27,279 --> 00:27:29,143
- Bye.
- Bye.

353
00:27:29,143 --> 00:27:30,623
So what are we eating?

354
00:27:30,623 --> 00:27:34,921
After bonding with fish all day,
please don't tell me we're having sashimi.

355
00:27:35,862 --> 00:27:37,400
Alright, everybody, cheers!

356
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,647
- Great work today.
- Cheers.

357
00:27:38,647 --> 00:27:41,180
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

358
00:27:47,941 --> 00:27:51,154
We were just friends a minute ago.

359
00:27:51,154 --> 00:27:53,194
Farewell, my little fishies.

360
00:27:54,972 --> 00:27:56,929
Ma'am, you're hilarious.

361
00:27:56,929 --> 00:27:58,255
Right?

362
00:28:00,805 --> 00:28:02,886
These are different fish from the ones earlier,

363
00:28:02,886 --> 00:28:04,735
so eat up guilt-free.

364
00:28:04,735 --> 00:28:06,968
The ssamjang here is amazing.

365
00:28:13,980 --> 00:28:15,567
Good?

366
00:28:20,217 --> 00:28:22,277
Mr. Noh, here.

367
00:28:23,424 --> 00:28:25,688
- What?
- Oh, don't be shy.

368
00:28:25,688 --> 00:28:27,194
Here.

369
00:28:37,252 --> 00:28:39,362
Wow, this is so good.

370
00:28:39,362 --> 00:28:41,768
You're amazing at making wraps.

371
00:28:41,768 --> 00:28:45,015
Where'd you learn to wrap them like this?

372
00:28:45,015 --> 00:28:46,921
This is incredible.

373
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:14,883
It looks like he drank nearly
a lethal amount of alcohol.

374
00:29:14,883 --> 00:29:17,230
If you'd arrived any later,

375
00:29:17,230 --> 00:29:19,122
he could've died.

376
00:29:46,220 --> 00:29:48,301
That's never going to happen.

377
00:29:49,107 --> 00:29:51,740
Us going back to how things were.

378
00:29:53,649 --> 00:29:55,402
So...

379
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:59,293
I'm never going back to you.

380
00:30:21,191 --> 00:30:23,567
Did you and Director Lee start together?

381
00:30:23,567 --> 00:30:25,111
Yeah, one of my few surviving work buddies.

382
00:30:25,111 --> 00:30:27,362
Exactly. When you spend this long at a company,

383
00:30:27,362 --> 00:30:29,544
there's nobody you rely on
more than the people you started with.

384
00:30:29,544 --> 00:30:31,833
Most of mine took early retirement, and...

385
00:30:31,833 --> 00:30:32,869
Hey!

386
00:30:32,869 --> 00:30:35,513
- Long time no see.
- Hello, have a seat.

387
00:30:35,513 --> 00:30:40,389
Sir, this is Yoon Sang Ho from
the Global Team at Haemu International.

388
00:30:40,389 --> 00:30:41,994
This is Team Leader Moo Gwang Il from Audit.

389
00:30:41,994 --> 00:30:43,454
Pleasure to meet you.

390
00:30:43,454 --> 00:30:45,583
Oh, funny running into
so many people from Audit today.

391
00:30:45,583 --> 00:30:48,387
I literally just came from diving with
Head Joo In Ah and

392
00:30:48,387 --> 00:30:52,514
Mr. Noh Ki Jun at the company scuba club.

393
00:30:52,514 --> 00:30:54,264
Oh, I see.

394
00:30:54,264 --> 00:30:55,587
Let me pour you a drink.

395
00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:57,767
Actually, I drove here,
so let me pour for you instead.

396
00:30:57,767 --> 00:30:59,769
- That's a shame.
- I'm good, thanks.

397
00:30:59,769 --> 00:31:02,116
Wait, didn't you drive here too?

398
00:31:02,116 --> 00:31:04,480
I'll just call a driver.

399
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:07,006
- It's an honor to meet you.
- Likewise.

400
00:31:10,843 --> 00:31:13,079
What's Assistant Manager Ha's deal?

401
00:31:13,079 --> 00:31:15,483
She was all over Mr. Min earlier,

402
00:31:15,483 --> 00:31:18,049
and now she seems interested in you too.

403
00:31:18,049 --> 00:31:20,559
Well, me...

404
00:31:20,559 --> 00:31:22,999
I do tend to attract attention.

405
00:31:22,999 --> 00:31:26,545
So she's the type who likes attention from men?

406
00:31:27,459 --> 00:31:29,363
Not men. Me.

407
00:31:29,363 --> 00:31:31,075
Because I'm me.

408
00:31:31,075 --> 00:31:33,215
Noh Ki Jun. Yeah?

409
00:31:34,329 --> 00:31:36,175
Oh, look at them.

410
00:31:42,761 --> 00:31:47,454
She's loading her gear into his car.

411
00:31:48,623 --> 00:31:51,109
Something's going on.

412
00:32:00,532 --> 00:32:02,408
Wait... what?

413
00:32:02,408 --> 00:32:05,177
She just left the gear and walked off.

414
00:32:05,177 --> 00:32:06,211
Yeah.

415
00:32:06,211 --> 00:32:09,508
Looks like Mr. Min got a call
and got pulled away somewhere.

416
00:32:11,632 --> 00:32:13,599
Then where'd Assistant Manager Ha go?

417
00:32:30,176 --> 00:32:31,993
I'm really sorry.

418
00:32:31,993 --> 00:32:35,290
I get super carsick,
so I can't sit in the back.

419
00:32:35,290 --> 00:32:38,147
And that seat's technically
the seat of honor, right?

420
00:32:38,147 --> 00:32:40,213
You're my superior after all.

421
00:32:40,213 --> 00:32:41,872
Thank you so much.

422
00:32:41,872 --> 00:32:43,896
By the way,

423
00:32:43,896 --> 00:32:46,276
Mr. Noh, where do you live?

424
00:32:47,254 --> 00:32:48,919
Is it near my place?

425
00:32:50,392 --> 00:32:52,770
I just feel bad
if I'm making you drive out of your way.

426
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:54,708
No, it's fine.

427
00:32:56,376 --> 00:32:58,013
But honestly...

428
00:33:00,074 --> 00:33:03,706
doesn't it get annoying
doing club activities with your boss too?

429
00:33:03,706 --> 00:33:06,022
Wow, I can hear all of that.

430
00:33:06,022 --> 00:33:07,786
Oh, sorry.

431
00:33:08,722 --> 00:33:10,944
I mean, Mr. Min has it rough too,

432
00:33:10,944 --> 00:33:14,890
doing club activities with Manager Yoon
from the same team.

433
00:33:20,715 --> 00:33:25,052
You and Mr. Min must be really close then.

434
00:33:25,052 --> 00:33:27,195
You two were talking nonstop earlier,

435
00:33:27,195 --> 00:33:31,075
And you keep bringing him up even now...

436
00:33:31,075 --> 00:33:32,215
Oh my gosh.

437
00:33:33,715 --> 00:33:36,552
You totally got the wrong idea.

438
00:33:36,552 --> 00:33:39,698
He's married and has a kid.

439
00:33:39,698 --> 00:33:41,843
And we're actually cousins.

440
00:33:41,843 --> 00:33:44,662
We just happened to join the same club.

441
00:33:44,662 --> 00:33:49,524
Oh... so Mr. Min and you are just relatives.

442
00:33:49,524 --> 00:33:54,055
Yes. That's why I leave my gear in his car.

443
00:33:54,055 --> 00:33:56,779
My gosh. This is actually hilarious.

444
00:33:56,779 --> 00:33:59,378
How did you even come up with that?

445
00:33:59,378 --> 00:34:00,450
Oh wow,

446
00:34:00,450 --> 00:34:02,869
you must work out a lot.

447
00:34:02,869 --> 00:34:05,288
Wow, this is hilarious.

448
00:34:05,288 --> 00:34:07,332
We almost got the wrong idea
about Mr. Min and you.

449
00:34:07,332 --> 00:34:08,989
This is way too funny.

450
00:34:08,989 --> 00:34:11,411
Seriously. Wow!

451
00:34:17,118 --> 00:34:19,921
So anyway, that rookie punk

452
00:34:19,921 --> 00:34:22,966
ended up storming into HR
and making a huge scene,

453
00:34:22,966 --> 00:34:27,149
and Director Lee got shipped off
to a branch office.

454
00:34:27,149 --> 00:34:31,013
Seriously, these days everything's
"gaslighting" this, "toxic" that.

455
00:34:31,013 --> 00:34:33,193
Kids these days learn
all the wrong stuff online.

456
00:34:33,193 --> 00:34:35,341
Still, I'm sure there were circumstances...

457
00:34:35,341 --> 00:34:37,199
Come on, circumstances or not.

458
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:40,420
Since when does a rookie
get to take down their boss?

459
00:34:40,420 --> 00:34:42,033
Does that make any sense?

460
00:34:42,033 --> 00:34:43,077
- Sir,
- Yes?

461
00:34:43,077 --> 00:34:45,038
in military terms,

462
00:34:45,038 --> 00:34:49,712
that's like a private taking out
a division commander.

463
00:34:49,712 --> 00:34:51,668
The military and office life aren't the same.

464
00:34:51,668 --> 00:34:53,491
What's so different about them?

465
00:34:53,491 --> 00:34:56,220
They're both organizations with ranks.

466
00:34:56,220 --> 00:35:01,299
What I'm saying is,
there should be a proper chain of command.

467
00:35:01,299 --> 00:35:05,376
You're on the global team,
but somehow you sound even more old-school

468
00:35:05,376 --> 00:35:08,351
than our old-fashioned Audit guys.

469
00:35:08,351 --> 00:35:09,727
Well, I am an old guy.

470
00:35:09,727 --> 00:35:12,438
In our team, when we drink,
we don't touch this stuff.

471
00:35:12,438 --> 00:35:16,171
Only the strong soju with the red caps.
Old-school style.

472
00:35:16,171 --> 00:35:18,618
It's gotten pretty late already.
I should get going.

473
00:35:18,618 --> 00:35:19,749
- You heading out?
- Yeah.

474
00:35:19,749 --> 00:35:21,586
I'll say goodbye to Director Lee and head out.

475
00:35:21,586 --> 00:35:23,150
- Take your time.
- Okay.

476
00:35:23,150 --> 00:35:24,976
- Take care, sir.
- Bye.

477
00:35:28,243 --> 00:35:29,831
Today at the club...

478
00:35:29,831 --> 00:35:31,653
Didn't I tell you to learn scuba diving?

479
00:35:31,653 --> 00:35:35,848
I'm practically connected now with
the legendary Joo In Ah from Audit.

480
00:35:35,848 --> 00:35:38,501
I'll introduce you sometime soon.

481
00:35:38,501 --> 00:35:40,613
Team Leader Moo's got zero pull.

482
00:35:40,613 --> 00:35:43,363
That guy's never making executive.

483
00:35:43,363 --> 00:35:45,110
Still, he's a good person.

484
00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:48,103
What good does that do anybody?

485
00:35:49,597 --> 00:35:51,874
Hold on.

486
00:35:51,874 --> 00:35:53,594
Yeah, you here?

487
00:35:53,594 --> 00:35:56,491
Yeah, come over to my car.

488
00:35:56,491 --> 00:35:58,484
My driver just got here.

489
00:35:58,484 --> 00:35:59,613
Alright, go ahead.

490
00:36:02,615 --> 00:36:07,237
Listening to him trash people for hours
really leaves a bad taste in your mouth.

491
00:36:10,289 --> 00:36:11,840
Wait,

492
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:14,540
isn't that the scuba diving guy?

493
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:16,540
Who's he waiting for?

494
00:36:24,974 --> 00:36:26,519
Oh my...

495
00:36:26,519 --> 00:36:29,578
The Manager Yoon called over was Mr. Min?

496
00:36:29,578 --> 00:36:31,561
Not a designated driver?

497
00:36:31,561 --> 00:36:33,501
Wow, that guy really is...

498
00:36:35,198 --> 00:36:37,635
I knew it the second
he started badmouthing people.

499
00:36:37,635 --> 00:36:40,021
Guy's bad news.

500
00:36:42,681 --> 00:36:43,992
Ki Jun, it's me.

501
00:36:43,992 --> 00:36:45,936
You know that Manager Yoon
from the global team?

502
00:36:45,936 --> 00:36:47,796
Yeah, he's bad news.

503
00:36:58,992 --> 00:37:00,426
Sir?

504
00:37:01,165 --> 00:37:02,926
- Sir...
- Yeah.

505
00:37:03,623 --> 00:37:05,803
Man, I drank too much.

506
00:37:05,803 --> 00:37:07,323
Hold on.

507
00:37:22,347 --> 00:37:24,618
- Hey, give me that.
- Yes.

508
00:37:24,618 --> 00:37:26,901
Oh right. Hold on.

509
00:37:28,159 --> 00:37:29,529
Drink this before you go inside.

510
00:37:29,529 --> 00:37:31,989
That's why you're my Native.

511
00:37:31,989 --> 00:37:33,989
You've got instincts.

512
00:37:40,270 --> 00:37:42,101
- Native.
- Yes, sir?

513
00:37:42,101 --> 00:37:44,251
I'm telling you,
I'll take care of you to the very end.

514
00:37:44,251 --> 00:37:45,751
Just trust me and stick with me.

515
00:37:45,751 --> 00:37:48,555
You know I'm the only one
in this company looking out for you.

516
00:37:48,555 --> 00:37:50,255
Of course, sir.

517
00:37:50,255 --> 00:37:53,319
I'm always grateful for
everything you do for me.

518
00:37:53,319 --> 00:37:55,625
Give me that. Now get home.

519
00:37:57,912 --> 00:37:59,405
Oh, sir...

520
00:38:00,358 --> 00:38:01,875
About...

521
00:38:01,875 --> 00:38:04,413
the dive next Saturday...

522
00:38:04,413 --> 00:38:06,132
Why?

523
00:38:06,132 --> 00:38:07,240
You can't make it?

524
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:08,894
It's just...

525
00:38:08,894 --> 00:38:11,292
my daughter's preschool is
having a cooking class...

526
00:38:11,292 --> 00:38:13,119
Then who am I supposed to dive with?

527
00:38:13,119 --> 00:38:15,246
I had to dive with
that damn club president today,

528
00:38:15,246 --> 00:38:16,536
and it was annoying as hell.

529
00:38:16,536 --> 00:38:19,260
Every time I wandered off, he dragged me back,

530
00:38:19,260 --> 00:38:20,962
and he wouldn't stop shaking that damn rattle.

531
00:38:20,962 --> 00:38:24,177
Is it too much for you?
Diving with me every week?

532
00:38:24,177 --> 00:38:27,547
- Are you forcing yourself or something?
- Of course not, sir.

533
00:38:27,547 --> 00:38:30,391
Thanks to you, I got into such a great hobby.

534
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:32,271
That's right, kid.

535
00:38:32,271 --> 00:38:34,195
Just stick with me.

536
00:38:34,195 --> 00:38:36,788
You're supposed to make manager this round,
aren't you?

537
00:38:36,788 --> 00:38:39,888
You said you're the only one left
out of your whole class.

538
00:38:39,888 --> 00:38:42,099
Yes, sir.

539
00:38:42,099 --> 00:38:43,329
I'll work even harder.

540
00:38:43,329 --> 00:38:46,627
Don't just work hard.

541
00:38:46,627 --> 00:38:48,540
Work smart.

542
00:38:49,882 --> 00:38:51,616
Yes, sir. I will.

543
00:38:51,616 --> 00:38:53,829
Yeah, that's my Native.

544
00:38:53,829 --> 00:38:56,579
- Get inside.
- Yes, sir. Good night.

545
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:11,377
Mr. Min.

546
00:39:20,448 --> 00:39:23,545
He kept calling you "Native."

547
00:39:23,545 --> 00:39:24,901
What's that supposed to mean?

548
00:39:24,901 --> 00:39:28,675
Everyone on our team studied
or worked overseas, except me.

549
00:39:28,675 --> 00:39:33,048
So they call me "Native"
because I'm a Korean native speaker.

550
00:39:35,686 --> 00:39:38,236
Doesn't sound like a very flattering nickname.

551
00:39:38,236 --> 00:39:41,026
Mr. Min, we saw everything.

552
00:39:41,026 --> 00:39:43,806
You acting like Manager Yoon's chauffeur.

553
00:39:43,806 --> 00:39:46,584
And the whole scuba diving thing
that clearly isn't your thing...

554
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:48,361
That's for Manager Yoon too, isn't it?

555
00:39:48,361 --> 00:39:50,466
I'm just surviving at work.

556
00:39:50,466 --> 00:39:52,051
Everyone puts up with this kind of stuff.

557
00:39:52,051 --> 00:39:53,699
No, Mr. Min.

558
00:39:53,699 --> 00:39:56,776
That's workplace harassment.

559
00:39:56,776 --> 00:39:58,129
She's right.

560
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:01,686
You should be honest about it this time.

561
00:40:01,686 --> 00:40:03,859
- With your wife too.
- My wife?

562
00:40:04,933 --> 00:40:06,957
No. Absolutely not.

563
00:40:06,957 --> 00:40:09,860
But your wife thinks
you're having an affair right now.

564
00:40:09,860 --> 00:40:11,874
Honestly, I'd rather she think that.

565
00:40:11,874 --> 00:40:12,970
What?

566
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:17,053
I don't want my wife finding out

567
00:40:18,310 --> 00:40:20,827
that this is how I survive at work.

568
00:40:32,766 --> 00:40:34,557
This doesn't feel like something

569
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:36,956
we should just let slide.

570
00:40:36,956 --> 00:40:40,446
This goes beyond a simple power dynamic.
It's basically gaslighting.

571
00:40:40,446 --> 00:40:43,181
I get why he wouldn't want his family knowing.

572
00:40:43,181 --> 00:40:47,413
Let's just tell his wife
there was no evidence of an affair.

573
00:40:47,413 --> 00:40:48,597
Okay.

574
00:40:48,597 --> 00:40:53,561
And I think we need to separate him
from Manager Yoon as soon as possible.

575
00:40:53,561 --> 00:40:55,803
I'll think of a way.

576
00:40:57,801 --> 00:41:01,428
This isn't something
we should have to deal with alone.

577
00:41:02,354 --> 00:41:05,585
There has to be something the company can do.

578
00:41:17,643 --> 00:41:20,355
Alright, we're here.

579
00:41:20,355 --> 00:41:23,840
Try not to think about it anymore.
Just get some rest.

580
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:26,680
You must be exhausted after diving all day.

581
00:41:27,386 --> 00:41:28,655
Mr. Noh.

582
00:41:30,426 --> 00:41:32,519
Want to come up for ramen?

583
00:41:54,763 --> 00:41:57,068
Three minutes are up.

584
00:41:57,068 --> 00:42:00,001
Here, eat your ramen while you work.

585
00:42:00,628 --> 00:42:01,978
Man...

586
00:42:01,978 --> 00:42:05,578
Since when did
"Want to come up for ramen?" turn into

587
00:42:05,578 --> 00:42:08,715
"Pull an all-nighter working
while eating ramen?"

588
00:42:08,715 --> 00:42:11,981
That changed a long time ago.
You seriously didn't know?

589
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:14,920
Here, enjoy.

590
00:42:16,204 --> 00:42:19,535
And it's not even real ramen. It's cup noodles.

591
00:42:19,535 --> 00:42:21,367
No kimchi, no pickled radish, nothing.

592
00:42:21,367 --> 00:42:24,485
Wow, you actually
pulled this together pretty fast.

593
00:42:24,485 --> 00:42:26,702
But this definition section feels vague.

594
00:42:26,702 --> 00:42:29,349
It'd be better to cite the regulations.

595
00:42:29,349 --> 00:42:32,294
And for this case,
it'd work better as more of a narrative.

596
00:42:32,294 --> 00:42:34,727
Can you visualize it with some images?

597
00:42:38,086 --> 00:42:40,167
Can I at least have time to eat my ramen?

598
00:42:40,167 --> 00:42:41,979
But isn't this case a little too extreme?

599
00:42:41,979 --> 00:42:44,759
I think we need something more relatable.

600
00:42:47,351 --> 00:42:49,437
Fine. Which case?

601
00:42:49,437 --> 00:42:50,745
This one.

602
00:42:50,745 --> 00:42:54,265
Workplace harassment starts quietly.

603
00:42:54,265 --> 00:42:56,602
With a passing comment every morning.

604
00:42:56,602 --> 00:42:59,102
A certain look in someone's eyes.

605
00:42:59,102 --> 00:43:00,906
Little by little,
you get excluded from the team.

606
00:43:00,906 --> 00:43:03,686
Unreasonable overtime becomes "expected."

607
00:43:03,686 --> 00:43:05,577
"You should know how to handle that yourself."

608
00:43:05,577 --> 00:43:09,472
And then one day, suddenly...
"Why do you do everything your way?"

609
00:43:11,456 --> 00:43:13,246
But the scariest part is this.

610
00:43:13,246 --> 00:43:17,406
The longer it goes on,
the more that person starts doubting themselves.

611
00:43:17,406 --> 00:43:19,199
"Am I really the problem?"

612
00:43:19,199 --> 00:43:20,509
"Am I being too sensitive?"

613
00:43:20,509 --> 00:43:23,163
"Do people just not like me?"

614
00:43:23,163 --> 00:43:26,889
That anxiety is what makes
people accept the unacceptable.

615
00:43:30,364 --> 00:43:32,162
Everyone,

616
00:43:32,162 --> 00:43:35,028
what's unacceptable always belongs
to the abuser.

617
00:43:35,028 --> 00:43:37,872
Don't doubt yourself. Don't hesitate.
And don't hide it.

618
00:43:37,872 --> 00:43:39,545
Report it.

619
00:43:40,475 --> 00:43:42,892
The company has a responsibility

620
00:43:42,892 --> 00:43:45,681
to protect and support all of you,
our valuable employees.

621
00:43:46,548 --> 00:43:47,811
Understood?

622
00:43:47,811 --> 00:43:49,464
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

623
00:43:53,584 --> 00:43:55,463
Mr. Noh.

624
00:43:56,706 --> 00:43:59,209
- Hello, Mr. Min.
- Hello.

625
00:43:59,898 --> 00:44:03,244
I got assigned to the U.S. branch this time.

626
00:44:04,105 --> 00:44:05,983
Congratulations.

627
00:44:05,983 --> 00:44:08,653
I heard that was supposed to be your spot.

628
00:44:08,653 --> 00:44:10,454
I hope you didn't give it up because of me.

629
00:44:10,454 --> 00:44:13,026
That's not something you can just give away.

630
00:44:13,026 --> 00:44:16,693
You got it because you earned it.

631
00:44:16,693 --> 00:44:18,010
Thank you.

632
00:44:18,010 --> 00:44:21,583
I also heard Manager Yoon got disciplined.

633
00:44:21,583 --> 00:44:23,993
- That wasn't because of me, was it?
- No.

634
00:44:23,993 --> 00:44:28,621
He got caught sneaking off
to go diving during a business trip.

635
00:44:28,621 --> 00:44:30,120
That's all it was.

636
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,347
So don't worry about it.

637
00:44:32,347 --> 00:44:33,746
I see.

638
00:44:34,436 --> 00:44:36,068
Have a safe trip on your assignment.

639
00:44:36,068 --> 00:44:38,141
Get some proper rest while you're there too.

640
00:44:38,141 --> 00:44:39,645
Thank you.

641
00:44:39,645 --> 00:44:42,525
My wife's really happy about it too.

642
00:44:42,525 --> 00:44:44,185
I'll do my best.

643
00:44:45,838 --> 00:44:47,593
Oh, and...

644
00:44:47,593 --> 00:44:49,712
you two look good together.

645
00:44:49,712 --> 00:44:50,922
What?

646
00:45:02,983 --> 00:45:06,614
You notice a lot of things underwater.

647
00:45:06,614 --> 00:45:09,918
Even while you were diving with me,

648
00:45:09,918 --> 00:45:12,663
your attention was always on Head Joo.

649
00:45:12,663 --> 00:45:15,562
You kept my secret safe,

650
00:45:15,562 --> 00:45:17,795
so I'll keep yours too.

651
00:45:17,795 --> 00:45:19,333
Don't worry.

652
00:45:19,333 --> 00:45:21,066
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

653
00:45:25,466 --> 00:45:27,386
Nice shot!

654
00:45:28,412 --> 00:45:31,619
- You're ready for a real course now.
- Thank you, sir.

655
00:45:31,619 --> 00:45:34,783
I think I play better when you teach me.

656
00:45:34,783 --> 00:45:36,200
Oh right.

657
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:38,258
I checked into the Haemu Pharma case,

658
00:45:38,258 --> 00:45:40,250
but there was nothing handed over to me.

659
00:45:40,250 --> 00:45:41,477
Really?

660
00:45:41,477 --> 00:45:44,750
They went through all that trouble
auditing the place

661
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:46,500
and left behind nothing?

662
00:45:46,500 --> 00:45:48,081
No, sir.

663
00:45:48,081 --> 00:45:49,559
Are you paying extra attention to it

664
00:45:49,559 --> 00:45:53,501
because the former CEO of Haemu Pharma
was Vice Chairman Jae Yeol?

665
00:45:54,712 --> 00:45:56,124
Who knows.

666
00:45:59,766 --> 00:46:02,177
Nice shot! Lucky bounce!

667
00:46:02,177 --> 00:46:03,734
That's close!

668
00:46:05,888 --> 00:46:08,093
Who's calling me right now?

669
00:46:10,355 --> 00:46:12,038
Yeah, what is it?

670
00:46:14,228 --> 00:46:16,092
Really?

671
00:46:16,092 --> 00:46:18,092
My sister-in-law came by?

672
00:46:47,506 --> 00:46:49,689
Haven't seen you in a while.

673
00:46:49,689 --> 00:46:52,193
You actually look pretty cute asleep.

674
00:46:52,193 --> 00:46:54,133
I heard you were sick.

675
00:46:54,133 --> 00:46:56,717
Acute alcohol poisoning?

676
00:46:56,717 --> 00:47:00,703
You told me to get treatment for addiction,
and now look at you.

677
00:47:03,469 --> 00:47:04,760
When did you get here?

678
00:47:04,760 --> 00:47:09,710
Dad told me to come check on you
since you looked like a complete wreck.

679
00:47:10,447 --> 00:47:12,296
But what was that about?

680
00:47:13,821 --> 00:47:16,809
I mean,
it's not like you missed me or anything.

681
00:47:18,156 --> 00:47:21,919
Were you pissed because your bro
got named co-vice chairman?

682
00:47:21,919 --> 00:47:24,005
God, seriously.

683
00:47:27,272 --> 00:47:30,076
What's with you? You're no fun today.

684
00:47:30,076 --> 00:47:31,421
Hyun Young.

685
00:47:32,619 --> 00:47:34,746
Yeah?

686
00:47:34,746 --> 00:47:36,283
Let's stop.

687
00:47:36,283 --> 00:47:37,832
Stop what?

688
00:47:42,722 --> 00:47:44,386
Let's get divorced.

689
00:47:44,386 --> 00:47:46,859
What the hell are you talking about?

690
00:47:46,859 --> 00:47:48,436
Why would we get divorced?

691
00:47:48,436 --> 00:47:50,622
You're unhappy with me too.

692
00:47:52,118 --> 00:47:54,564
Let's just let each other go.

693
00:47:55,963 --> 00:47:58,268
When you've made up your mind, tell me.

694
00:47:58,993 --> 00:48:01,549
The rest can go through the lawyers.

695
00:48:05,740 --> 00:48:08,544
Hey, at least give me a reason.

696
00:48:08,544 --> 00:48:11,954
What, did you marry me for love or something?

697
00:48:11,954 --> 00:48:13,874
Why are you suddenly acting like this?

698
00:48:13,874 --> 00:48:16,291
Did you finally lose it? Like your mother?

699
00:48:18,572 --> 00:48:21,287
I just don't want to live like this anymore.

700
00:48:22,993 --> 00:48:24,365
You know...

701
00:48:26,307 --> 00:48:29,720
If you divorce me,
your shot at succession is over.

702
00:48:31,661 --> 00:48:33,185
Hyun Young,

703
00:48:34,721 --> 00:48:37,130
I'll figure out my own path.

704
00:48:37,747 --> 00:48:39,232
Please.

705
00:48:40,133 --> 00:48:41,990
Just divorce me.

706
00:48:57,944 --> 00:48:59,474
Hey.

707
00:48:59,474 --> 00:49:01,537
Something's seriously wrong with my husband.

708
00:49:02,771 --> 00:49:04,888
Can you dig into what's going on?

709
00:49:11,924 --> 00:49:13,161
When are you getting off work?

710
00:49:13,161 --> 00:49:15,700
Come over for dinner tonight.

711
00:49:15,700 --> 00:49:18,638
Why? So you can make me eat ramen
while working again?

712
00:49:25,063 --> 00:49:27,443
No, tonight's for real.

713
00:49:33,484 --> 00:49:35,848
Alright, everyone. Good work today.

714
00:49:35,848 --> 00:49:37,995
- Good work.
- Good work.

715
00:49:41,628 --> 00:49:44,191
Did she just wink at me?

716
00:49:44,191 --> 00:49:45,618
You sure you didn't imagine that?

717
00:49:45,618 --> 00:49:48,431
Maybe something just got in her eye.

718
00:49:48,431 --> 00:49:51,077
No, seriously.

719
00:49:52,491 --> 00:49:54,945
- She totally did this.
- Wait...

720
00:49:54,945 --> 00:49:57,488
- What if it's some kind of signal?
- Like...

721
00:49:57,488 --> 00:49:59,452
"Congrats, you're pulling overtime tomorrow?"

722
00:49:59,452 --> 00:50:01,552
Come on, maybe her eyes were just tired.

723
00:50:01,552 --> 00:50:03,043
Quit talking nonsense.

724
00:50:03,043 --> 00:50:04,112
Anyway...

725
00:50:04,112 --> 00:50:08,460
Since Ki Jun got discharged,
we still haven't had a proper team dinner.

726
00:50:08,460 --> 00:50:10,920
Let's go eat something good tonight.

727
00:50:10,920 --> 00:50:12,725
- Sounds good.
- I'm in.

728
00:50:12,725 --> 00:50:14,115
Ms. Yoon, you coming?

729
00:50:14,115 --> 00:50:16,335
Depends on the food.

730
00:50:16,335 --> 00:50:19,106
Wow, since when do you join team dinners?

731
00:50:20,008 --> 00:50:22,672
Guess we really need to eat
something good tonight.

732
00:50:22,672 --> 00:50:26,010
I'll put it on the company card for once.

733
00:50:26,010 --> 00:50:27,644
Buying with the company card?

734
00:50:27,644 --> 00:50:28,906
Nice. Love it.

735
00:50:28,906 --> 00:50:30,754
- Let's go, let's go.
- Wait!

736
00:50:32,627 --> 00:50:34,598
Sorry, but tonight...

737
00:50:35,947 --> 00:50:38,942
I really want to go, seriously, I do,

738
00:50:41,514 --> 00:50:43,887
but I already have important plans.

739
00:50:45,461 --> 00:50:47,220
Oh, got it.

740
00:50:48,262 --> 00:50:49,352
That's fine.

741
00:50:49,352 --> 00:50:51,485
Guess I'll just stay behind and work, then.

742
00:50:51,485 --> 00:50:52,504
Yeah...

743
00:50:54,630 --> 00:50:56,255
Might as well work too.

744
00:51:14,967 --> 00:51:17,680
What brings you all the way to the 14th floor?

745
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:20,284
I had something to deliver to Planning.

746
00:51:20,284 --> 00:51:21,552
I see.

747
00:51:36,007 --> 00:51:38,239
You must be having fun.

748
00:51:41,758 --> 00:51:43,730
Between two men...

749
00:51:47,851 --> 00:51:51,694
Which one are you actually upset about?

750
00:51:51,694 --> 00:51:55,137
If I told you, would you give one of them up?

751
00:51:55,900 --> 00:51:59,418
Because if you would, you can keep Ki Jun.

752
00:51:59,418 --> 00:52:01,851
You won't even have to.

753
00:52:03,074 --> 00:52:05,098
You and Ki Jun won't last anyway.

754
00:52:05,098 --> 00:52:08,031
That's just how he dates.

755
00:52:08,031 --> 00:52:09,891
He's shallow.

756
00:52:13,684 --> 00:52:15,098
And what?

757
00:52:15,830 --> 00:52:18,641
If I give up Jae Yeol,

758
00:52:18,641 --> 00:52:20,894
do you really think you could have him?

759
00:52:22,188 --> 00:52:24,645
I get that you're upset with me,

760
00:52:24,645 --> 00:52:26,265
but you should watch your tone.

761
00:52:26,265 --> 00:52:28,109
I may look young,

762
00:52:28,109 --> 00:52:30,375
but I'm still an executive at this company.

763
00:52:30,375 --> 00:52:32,512
Secretary Park Ah Jeong.

764
00:52:38,505 --> 00:52:39,910
Bye.

765
00:52:46,029 --> 00:52:49,562
- The White Blood Cell Show!
- Show!

766
00:52:56,166 --> 00:52:57,904
Hey, how do you even do that?

767
00:52:57,904 --> 00:53:00,878
You just open your throat wide...
and drop it straight in.

768
00:53:00,878 --> 00:53:02,202
Just give me a little more time.

769
00:53:02,202 --> 00:53:05,662
I'm just staying long enough to be polite,
then I'm out.

770
00:53:05,662 --> 00:53:07,115
That's awesome.

771
00:53:08,502 --> 00:53:11,042
How is that even possible?

772
00:53:11,987 --> 00:53:14,677
You should start a mukbang or something.

773
00:53:14,677 --> 00:53:16,994
Why is this meat taking forever?
Isn't the heat too low?

774
00:53:16,994 --> 00:53:18,574
No, the heat's all the way up.

775
00:53:18,574 --> 00:53:21,894
The meat's just really thick.

776
00:53:21,894 --> 00:53:23,643
Give it here. I'll do it.

777
00:53:23,643 --> 00:53:25,318
- No, it's okay. I'll grill it.
- No, it's fine.

778
00:53:25,318 --> 00:53:27,397
I'm on a diet anyway, so I'll do the grilling.

779
00:53:27,397 --> 00:53:29,921
Come on, give me that.

780
00:53:29,921 --> 00:53:32,595
Alright, everybody, eat up.

781
00:53:33,987 --> 00:53:35,685
Hurry and eat.

782
00:53:35,685 --> 00:53:36,906
Nice.

783
00:53:49,586 --> 00:53:52,371
Do you need a toothbrush or a razor too?

784
00:53:52,371 --> 00:53:55,027
- What?
- Wasn't tonight supposed to be your big night?

785
00:53:55,027 --> 00:53:58,187
You should at least grab a toothbrush.
For your boyfriend.

786
00:53:59,585 --> 00:54:02,244
It's been a while
since I've had a night like this.

787
00:54:02,244 --> 00:54:03,685
Where are the toothbrushes?

788
00:54:09,667 --> 00:54:11,117
Alright, alright.

789
00:54:11,117 --> 00:54:13,164
Come on, let's do another round.

790
00:54:13,164 --> 00:54:15,935
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

791
00:54:15,935 --> 00:54:18,148
Wow, you can really drink.

792
00:54:18,148 --> 00:54:20,619
- Sir, have another drink.
- Sure.

793
00:54:21,768 --> 00:54:23,374
Okay, let's go hard tonight.

794
00:54:25,881 --> 00:54:28,020
Let's go hard tonight!

795
00:54:32,695 --> 00:54:34,288
Alright. Cheers!

796
00:54:35,621 --> 00:54:37,486
Come on, cheers. Last round!

797
00:54:37,486 --> 00:54:40,894
- Last round!
- Last round!

798
00:54:44,052 --> 00:54:45,729
So where are we going for round two?

799
00:54:45,729 --> 00:54:46,882
Karaoke.

800
00:54:49,804 --> 00:54:51,883
- Oh, yes.
- Where is Ki Jun?

801
00:54:54,512 --> 00:54:57,250
Hey, where are you running off to?

802
00:54:57,250 --> 00:54:59,675
You're not leaving tonight.

803
00:54:59,675 --> 00:55:01,880
You're the man of the hour.
You can't bail on us now.

804
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:05,399
♪ I'm totally wasted ♪

805
00:55:05,399 --> 00:55:09,425
♪ Drunk out of my mind ♪

806
00:55:09,425 --> 00:55:15,704
♪ Lost in the scent of your love ♪

807
00:56:14,192 --> 00:56:15,618
Oh my gosh.

808
00:56:25,393 --> 00:56:26,830
Sorry.

809
00:56:26,830 --> 00:56:30,230
They're seriously holding me hostage tonight.

810
00:56:30,230 --> 00:56:35,227
I think I'm going to be
a little later than I thought.

811
00:56:35,227 --> 00:56:37,024
Oh, really?

812
00:56:37,024 --> 00:56:38,597
Well, nothing we can do.

813
00:56:38,597 --> 00:56:41,626
Work dinners are basically work anyway.
Take your time.

814
00:56:45,317 --> 00:56:48,241
Guess he won't be hungry then.

815
00:56:48,241 --> 00:56:51,206
So I'll just eat by myself...

816
00:56:51,206 --> 00:56:54,932
I'll probably gain weight, but whatever.

817
00:57:00,894 --> 00:57:02,168
What?

818
00:57:04,517 --> 00:57:06,944
Did he lie about being late?

819
00:57:06,944 --> 00:57:09,277
What is this, a surprise?

820
00:57:10,757 --> 00:57:12,738
How are you here already?

821
00:57:23,396 --> 00:57:26,443
♪ I'm totally wasted ♪

822
00:57:29,736 --> 00:57:31,426
Alright, you can go.

823
00:57:32,101 --> 00:57:33,914
Just one more...

824
00:57:34,846 --> 00:57:36,431
Okay, okay.

825
00:57:36,431 --> 00:57:40,038
Then let's just have one more drink
with Ki Jun.

826
00:57:40,038 --> 00:57:41,882
Sounds good. I just need one last drink too.

827
00:57:41,882 --> 00:57:43,538
- I love it.
- No, no.

828
00:57:43,538 --> 00:57:45,042
That's enough for tonight. Next time.

829
00:57:45,042 --> 00:57:46,416
What do you mean "next time?"

830
00:57:46,416 --> 00:57:48,206
Tonight's all we've got.

831
00:57:48,206 --> 00:57:50,197
- Ki Jun!
- Just one more drink.

832
00:57:50,197 --> 00:57:52,437
- Next time!
- Hey!

833
00:57:57,052 --> 00:57:59,135
Looks like you were waiting for someone.

834
00:57:59,135 --> 00:58:03,048
I'd appreciate it
if you kept it short and left.

835
00:58:04,735 --> 00:58:07,219
This is probably a stupid thing to say,

836
00:58:07,219 --> 00:58:10,079
but even after marrying someone else,

837
00:58:10,079 --> 00:58:12,784
I never once felt like I'd lost you.

838
00:58:14,666 --> 00:58:16,782
That's incredibly selfish.

839
00:58:16,782 --> 00:58:19,596
That thing you said...
that you'd always be on my side.

840
00:58:20,864 --> 00:58:23,182
I think I lived clinging to just that.

841
00:58:23,980 --> 00:58:25,737
You called it loyalty, right?

842
00:58:26,836 --> 00:58:28,836
I don't care what it was.

843
00:58:31,480 --> 00:58:33,170
I'm getting divorced.

844
00:58:33,170 --> 00:58:35,143
I already told my wife.

845
00:58:40,474 --> 00:58:43,124
What exactly do you expect me to say to that?

846
00:58:43,124 --> 00:58:45,754
Were you hoping I'd go,

847
00:58:45,754 --> 00:58:49,938
"Wow, he's finally getting divorced.
I should date him now."

848
00:58:49,938 --> 00:58:51,022
Is that what you wanted to hear?

849
00:58:51,022 --> 00:58:54,487
I know. Even if I get divorced,
I can't get you back.

850
00:58:55,341 --> 00:58:59,334
I know I've really lost you now.

851
00:59:01,087 --> 00:59:04,834
But no matter what I do,
I can't let go of how I feel.

852
00:59:06,708 --> 00:59:09,351
So at least I wanted to be honest with myself.

853
00:59:10,038 --> 00:59:12,116
That's why I'm divorcing her.

854
00:59:12,802 --> 00:59:15,108
Not because of you. Because of me.

855
00:59:16,092 --> 00:59:18,085
Because I feel like I'm dying.

856
00:59:26,360 --> 00:59:29,027
I regret everything, In Ah.

857
00:59:35,769 --> 00:59:38,295
Sorry I'm so late.

858
00:59:44,251 --> 00:59:46,515
Looks like the person
you were waiting for is here.

859
00:59:47,912 --> 00:59:50,772
I said what I came to say, so I'll go.

860
01:00:28,120 --> 01:00:30,804
Wow, you really went all out.

861
01:00:32,014 --> 01:00:34,584
Did you make this pasta yourself?

862
01:00:34,584 --> 01:00:36,671
It looks good.

863
01:00:37,799 --> 01:00:39,772
I ordered delivery.

864
01:00:43,883 --> 01:00:46,046
Good call. Delivery's the best.

865
01:00:46,046 --> 01:00:49,820
When would the Head of Audit
ever have time to cook?

866
01:00:49,820 --> 01:00:52,633
You should spend that time
looking at me instead.

867
01:00:53,231 --> 01:00:54,924
You're not going to ask?

868
01:00:56,439 --> 01:00:58,317
You must feel awful.

869
01:00:58,317 --> 01:01:00,104
And curious too.

870
01:01:00,104 --> 01:01:02,948
Stop trying to change the subject
and just ask what you want to ask.

871
01:01:10,424 --> 01:01:12,250
Yeah, I'm curious.

872
01:01:12,250 --> 01:01:14,284
And I'm awful.

873
01:01:15,041 --> 01:01:16,951
But...

874
01:01:16,951 --> 01:01:19,166
I don't really want to ask.

875
01:01:19,764 --> 01:01:21,948
That's between you two.

876
01:01:31,539 --> 01:01:33,772
Guess tonight just isn't the night.

877
01:01:33,772 --> 01:01:35,974
You prepared all this too...

878
01:01:42,429 --> 01:01:45,432
Don't drink tonight. Just get some sleep.

879
01:01:45,432 --> 01:01:48,459
We both have work tomorrow, right?

880
01:01:50,152 --> 01:01:51,801
I should go.

881
01:02:53,970 --> 01:02:55,645
Don't go.

882
01:03:03,793 --> 01:03:06,082
Stay with me.

883
01:05:19,588 --> 01:05:21,145
Joo In Ah...

884
01:05:22,454 --> 01:05:25,447
What is that woman to you exactly?

885
01:05:26,634 --> 01:05:29,543
The kind of woman
that makes you want to die with her.

886
01:05:30,274 --> 01:05:33,051
You'd give up everything? For her?

887
01:05:33,051 --> 01:05:34,598
If I had to.

888
01:05:34,598 --> 01:05:37,322
If I gave up Jae Yeol,

889
01:05:37,322 --> 01:05:39,637
do you really think you could have him?

890
01:05:56,002 --> 01:05:57,279
Oh my,

891
01:05:57,279 --> 01:06:00,346
I almost ended up late. I never run late.

892
01:06:00,346 --> 01:06:03,863
Well, I never wear the same tie
two days in a row either.

893
01:06:03,863 --> 01:06:05,429
That's what dating does.

894
01:06:05,429 --> 01:06:07,944
Suddenly, things I never planned for
start popping up in my life.

895
01:06:07,944 --> 01:06:10,106
Wow, look at you talking smooth.

896
01:06:10,106 --> 01:06:12,427
Still, being late is unacceptable.

897
01:06:12,427 --> 01:06:14,567
Have a good day today.

898
01:06:16,540 --> 01:06:18,293
You too.

899
01:06:26,038 --> 01:06:29,244
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

900
01:06:31,524 --> 01:06:32,602
[New Message]

901
01:06:32,602 --> 01:06:33,804
[Reporting Joo In Ah]

902
01:06:46,956 --> 01:06:49,421
[Sender: NONAME]
[Reporting Joo In Ah]

903
01:06:58,232 --> 01:07:02,229
I'm reporting Joo In Ah's private life.

904
01:07:02,229 --> 01:07:07,446
She acts morally superior
while monitoring and punishing others,

905
01:07:07,446 --> 01:07:10,263
but her own private life is a mess.

906
01:07:10,263 --> 01:07:12,329
She's a hypocrite.

907
01:07:12,928 --> 01:07:14,770
Attached are...

908
01:07:14,770 --> 01:07:18,483
photos of Head Joo with her married superior.

909
01:08:48,756 --> 01:08:50,266
Head Joo... is that rumor true?

910
01:08:50,266 --> 01:08:53,853
So who is it? The man in that photo
you were supposedly greeting?

911
01:08:53,853 --> 01:08:56,279
Come on, even this is too much.

912
01:08:56,883 --> 01:08:58,810
Relax, you'll get wrinkles.

913
01:08:58,810 --> 01:09:01,020
I'll stand strong like a fortress! Let's go!

914
01:09:01,020 --> 01:09:02,494
Are you crying?

915
01:09:02,494 --> 01:09:04,003
About that email regarding Ms. Joo...

916
01:09:04,003 --> 01:09:07,450
The sender's location was traced
to Mr. Noh's home address.

917
01:09:07,450 --> 01:09:10,293
Are you going to swoop in like some prince
and carry me away?

918
01:09:10,293 --> 01:09:11,494
Then I'll say I did it.

919
01:09:11,494 --> 01:09:14,467
Assistant Manager Noh will be disciplined.

920
01:09:14,467 --> 01:09:17,087
I'll take responsibility.
